The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Briefs
                                                                                                                       7                                                                                                        
	Lausanne: Olympic and world 100 metres champion Shelly-Ann Fraser has tested positive for a painkiller she neglected to list on a doping form, the Jamaican stated on Thursday. She has been provisionally suspended by the IAAF pending a hearing.        
	Calcutta: Sukhendu Mondal of South 24 Parganas won the mens 200m event with a timing of 21.5s at the State Athletics Meet at the Salt Lake Stadium. He bettered the previous record of 21.6s jointly held by Ghulam Kibria and Rahamtullah Mollah. Soma Jana won the womens 100m hurdles.          
	Madrid: World No. 1 Rafael Nadal has become a shareholder at financially troubled Real Mallorca, the Spanish league side said on Thursday.           
	Brussels: A crowd of 35,681 at King Baudouin Stadium watched Kim Clijsters beat Serena Williams 6-3, 6-2 in an exhibition match on Thursday.         
	Glasgow: Jeev Milkha Singh put behind the shoulder injury and brought home a strong three-under 68 card to lie tied 12th after the opening round of the Scottish Open here.          
	New Delhi: Injured Olympic bronze medallist Vijender Singh will miss the 57th Mens National Boxing Championships after injuring his right hand during a sparring session.          
	New Delhi: The Decision Review System (DRS) will not be used in the India-Sri Lanka Test series starting on July 18 as the BCCI was not in favour of it, according to a Sri Lanka Cricket official.                                                                                                                                                        
